<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>16975</id>
	<title>Avoid creating container Id starting with digits</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Hello,</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">I have multiple time encountered an issue with the container which are assigned an ID starting with a digit.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">Indeed the container ID is also set as the host name of the container.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">Although I know that according to the RFCs it is acceptable a hostname to start with a digit I many time had issue with with application code that refuse such cases.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Is it possible to restrict this with an option or to simply change docker engine to always assign an ID starting with a letter?</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Thanks</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
